<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very close to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing in being always glabrous with shorter outer sepals and a white corolla limb. The seeds are densely uniformly pubescent, rather than woolly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
We have been cautious in accepting South American records of this species, which may have been confused with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="squamosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. squamosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
